With the National lockdown being a reality and families confined to their homes, it can get a little hectic with little ones succumbing to the monster of boredom and wreaking havoc around the home.  The Covid-19 pandemic and the lockdown is an unprecedented situation and nobody can tell when schools will open their doors again. Many schools have also asked parents to ensure that learning continues at home. Online learning is an obvious way to keep lessons going. Its easy for children to watching television or scroll online for hours but they are bound to get bored as the days go by. Here are some creative ways to banish the boredom at home and keep the little ones entertained.